b'Every day, we depend on our service men and women to keep us safe. And when they transition to civilian life, they far too often need to depend on us. Rob Bingham has made it his mission to build a community of support\xe2\x80\x94the Colorado Veterans Project\xe2\x80\x94that\xe2\x80\x99s there when veterans need it most. 

Colorado Veterans Project, Denver\xe2\x80\x99s largest nonprofit organization, helps veterans find aid with everything from PTSD and suicide prevention to job skills and resume writing. Rob\xe2\x80\x99s selfless attitude and hard work has made a huge impact on the Denver veteran community. As a thank you, we\xe2\x80\x99re proud to honor Rob as one of this year\xe2\x80\x99s Schwab Local Heroes.

b'As Elena Zee signed the mortgage for her first home, she noticed she didn\xe2\x80\x99t understand most of the words and terms in it. Worse, she worked in financial services and realized if it was this confusing for her then everyone else must be completely lost?

Now, as the president and CEO of The Arizona Council on Economic Education, Elena provides educational resources and support to teachers and parents across Arizona. Her mission is simple: improve financial education in schools, because financial literacy can quite literally change the trajectory of a child\xe2\x80\x99s life. We couldn\xe2\x80\x99t be happier to support her and the ACEE as a Schwab Local Hero.

b"@stefanieoconnell visited our #ownyourtomorrow mural by @sophie_roach and @colossalmedia in NYC! Check it out if you\xe2\x80\x99re in the area. #brooklyn #bushwick \xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb
When I was saving money to fly to Europe a few years ago :airplane_selector: , I struggled with the same day to day spending habits that always get in the of my savings efforts...\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
Not wanting to wait for the subway after a late night out and splurging on a cab :taxi: , or opting to pick up some of my favorite tacos :taco: for lunch instead of meal prepping ahead of time.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
But then I started to think about what those choices were costing me \xe2\x80\x93 that $10 here, 50 bucks there, 75 there:money_bag: \xe2\x80\x93 and over time, I started to see those numbers adding up, and saw that they were literally costing me the savings I needed to afford that trip to Europe. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
So I printed out a picture of my destination and I put it in my wallet wrapped around my cash and credit cards so that every time I considered making a purchase, I also had to consider the trade off of not saving up for my trip :money_with_wings:.
\xe2\xa0\x80
I had to think, am I really willing to give up this savings for my dream trip for some tacos I don\xe2\x80\x99t really need right now?\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
Within that framework, saving money was no longer about what I had to give up in the moment- tacos, it was about what I stood to gain big picture - Eurotrip. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
But it was only when I zoomed out to look at the big picture that I could start to see saving money through the lens of what it afforded me, and start making choices in service of those savings.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
How do you prioritize what you're saving for? \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
#ownyourtomorrow \xe2\xa0\x80"
